Q: What is Bespoke AI Laundry Combo?
A: Bespoke AI Laundry Combo is an all-in-one washer and dryer that lets you wash and dry in one machine without transferring loads. It's a simple "load once and finish" solution that saves space and is ideal for anyone who wants easier and seamless laundry.

Q: How does AI Wash & Dry work? 
A: AI Wash & Dry works by using different sensors to intelligently sense the fabric type, load weight, and soil level, then automatically adjusting water, detergent, wash time and drying settings to deliver a thorough wash and dry.

Q: How does AI Vision Inside enhance food management?
A: AI Vision Inside utilizes a built-in camera to help you stay organized by automatically tracking food items entering and exiting the fridge space. It also labels certain fresh foods, allowing you to monitor your groceries anytime from the Family Hub screen or your smartphone without opening the fridge door. You can also get recipe recommendations based on the ingredients you've selected from what's in your fridge.

Q. What is AI Hybrid Cooling?
A. It uses machine learning to predict the internal temperature 5 minutes after the fridge door is opened or closed. If additional cooling is needed, the Peltier system activates to keep the temperature stable.

title: How to use Smart Switch across Galaxy smartphones | Samsung
description:
This is the official video guide üìù on how to use Samsung Smart Switch to transfer data to your new Galaxy smartphone. Move contacts, photos, and more in no time! Smart Switch makes switching to Galaxy smartphone safe and easy. Learn more: http://smsng.co/Smart-Switch_yt

00:00 Intro 
00:15 Moving data from iOS using a cable
01:44 Moving data from iOS wirelessly
03:27 Moving data from Android wirelessly

Follow these simple steps to transfer your data with Smart Switch:
Step 1: Swipe up on your Home screen to open the Smart Switch app.
Step 2: Tap ‚ÄòReceive on this phone‚Äô and choose your old device type. 
Step 3: Connect both devices with a cable or wirelessly by scanning the QR code.
Step 4: Select the data you want to move.
Step 5: Wait for Smart Switch to complete the transfer.

Why use Samsung Smart Switch?
1. Data transfer across devices and OS: Move important data to a new Galaxy, whether you‚Äôre switching from iOS or Android.
2. Multiple transfer and backup options: Use a USB cable or wireless connection to back up and transfer your content. 
3. Wide range of data types: Transfer photos, videos, notes, calendar events, and even device settings to your Galaxy.

Q: What types of data can I transfer?
A: You can transfer contacts, messages, photos, videos, documents, and even device settings. Some iOS apps may not be transferred, but Smart Switch suggests similar apps for your new Galaxy device.
Q: Does Smart Switch delete content from my old phone?
A: No, Smart Switch does not remove any content from either device. After the transfer, your data stays on both devices.

title: How to work across Galaxy devices | Galaxy XR | Samsung
description:
This is the official video guide on how to work across Galaxy devices on Galaxy XR. Want to boost productivity? With Galaxy XR, you can connect your Galaxy Book to share your PC screen for smoother multi-tasking, and even take phone calls directly in XR‚Äîall without breaking your flow. It's perfect for remote workers, students, presenters, or anyone who wants to stay productive in any space‚Äîwhether you‚Äôre managing tasks, attending meetings, or simply working hands-free. Learn more: http://smsng.co/XR_Multi-Task_yt

00:00 Intro
00:11 Connecting Galaxy Book to Galaxy XR
01:00 Answering Galaxy smartphone calls on Galaxy XR

Follow these simple steps to use screen share on Galaxy XR:
Step 1: Check your setup. Make sure Galaxy XR and Galaxy Book are logged into the same Samsung account, with Wi-Fi and Bluetooth turned on. Your Galaxy Book should also have the Multi Control and Second Screen apps installed.
Step 2: Connect with 'PC Link'. In Galaxy XR settings, go to 'Connected devices' ‚Üí 'PC Link' and select your Galaxy Book.
Step 3: Start working in Galaxy XR. Your PC screen will appear in front of you‚Äîideal for tasks like photo editing, web browsing, or document work where a larger, immersive view makes you more efficient.

Follow these simple steps to take calls on Galaxy XR:
Step 1: Check your account. Make sure your Galaxy smartphone and Galaxy XR are logged into the same Samsung account, with Call on other devices enabled.
Step 2: Activate calling in settings. In Galaxy XR settings, go to 'Connected devices' ‚Üí 'Allow calling on this headset' and turn it on.
Step 3: Answer calls hands-free. Take calls directly with Galaxy XR while staying focused on your work.

Q: Can I connect Galaxy XR with all Galaxy devices?
A: This feature is available only on Galaxy Book running Windows 11 or later, and on Galaxy smartphones with Android P OS or later and at least 3 GB of RAM.
Q: What‚Äôs the benefit of the PC Link feature versus using a regular monitor?
A: The PC Link feature is ideal if you want a larger, immersive view and recommended if you need to multi-task across Galaxy XR and your Galaxy Book at the same time.

*Refrain from using the device while in motion within vehicles such as cars, buses, or trains. Using the device while in a moving vehicle may cause the tracking function to not work properly, rendering the device inoperable under these conditions.

title: Meet the Generation17 Young Leaders: The Story of Renata Koch Alvarenga | Samsung
description:
Read more about Renata and her story: http://smsng.co/Gen17_Renata_yt

Generation17 Young Leader Renata Koch Alvarenga has been fighting for climate justice‚Äîensuring equitable climate solutions for nearly a decade. When catastrophic floods devastated her home state in Brazil in 2024, it was a painful reminder of what she already knew: climate disasters hit the most vulnerable communities, including women and girls, the hardest. Through her organization, EmpoderaClima, Renata is building a powerful network of underrepresented climate leaders‚Äîtraining them in everything from disaster preparedness to climate advocacy. Her mission? Ensuring youth and women lead the fight for our planet's future.

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change, peace and justice, to build a better future for all by 2030. Be part of the solution‚Äîdownload the Samsung Global Goals app here: http://smsng.co/SGG-App_Renata_yt

Follow these steps to get the most of Sleep Coaching üí§:
Step 1: Wear your Galaxy Watch8 to bed‚Äîit records your sleep automatically.
Step 2: After at least 7 nights (including at least 1 workday and 1 day off), Sleep Coaching can be activated.
Step 3: Check Bedtime Guidance for tips on better sleep routines.
Step 4: In the morning, review your sleep report with stages and sleep score.
Step 5: Use Sleep Coaching‚Äôs program (multi-week plan) to improve long-term sleep habits.

Q: Do I need to activate Sleep Coaching every night?
A: No. Once set up, the watch records your sleep automatically.

Q: What‚Äôs the difference between Sleep Coaching and Bedtime Guidance?
A: Bedtime Guidance analyzes optimal bedtime every night and provides a notification 2 hours before bedtime, while Sleep Coaching provides a structured program with long-term improvement plans.

Q: Does Sleep Coaching influence Energy Score?
A: Sleep Coaching affects Energy Score, but not all of it. Energy Score is based on a comprehensive analysis, including not only sleep but also activity.

Follow these steps to get the most of Running Coach üèÉ:
Step 1: Set up your profile in Samsung Health.
Step 2: Take the Running Level Test‚Äîa 12-minute run with recovery assessment.
Step 3: Get assigned a Running Level from 1 to 10 based on your endurance.
Step 4: Receive a personalized multi-week training plan tailored to your level.
Step 5: Start running with real-time guidance on pace, cadence, distance, and heart rate.
Step 6: After your run, review detailed stats and feedback.
Step 7: Complete your plan and retake the test to move up toward higher levels

Q: Do I need to take a test before using Running Coach?
A: Yes‚Äîthe Running Level Test (12-minute run + recovery) determines your starting level.

Q: How is the training plan personalized?
A: Each level has its own multi-week plan with workouts (intervals, distance runs, recovery sessions) designed to match your ability.

Q: Do I get real-time coaching?
A: Yes‚Äîduring runs, you get live feedback on pace, distance, and heart rate so you stay on target.

Q: Can I level up over time?
A: Absolutely. Finish your current plan, retake the test, and progress up to Level 10 for more advanced training.

Follow these steps to get the most of Healthcare Coach ‚ù§Ô∏è:
Step 1: Wear your Galaxy Watch8 while you sleep‚Äîit uses the BioActive sensor to capture vascular data and AGEs Index.
Step 2: In the morning, check your Vascular Load to see how much stress your blood vessels experienced overnight and review your AGEs Index for long-term metabolic health insights.
Step 3: Measure your Antioxidant Index by placing your finger on the sensor for 5 seconds to detect carotenoid levels.
Step 4: Use these health metrics to adjust daily habits like sleep, diet, and activity.

Q: What is Vascular Load?

Q: What kind of workout plan does Running Coach offer?
A: Running Coach provides a structured 3 to 5 week plan that's customized to your fitness level. It provides real-time audio guidance from your watch to notify you about your pace, distance and progress toward your goal regardless whether you're a beginner or an experienced runner.

Q: What is RPE?
A: RPE stands for Rating of Perceived Exertion. It is an index that indicates the intensity you felt during the workout, from a scale of 1 to 10. Unlike objective stats like heart rate or speed, RPE reflects your condition subjectively.

description:

Q : How much energy can be saved with each product?
A : Refrigerators can achieve up to a global 15% energy savings in Step 1. Washing machines can save up to 70% for EU, 60% for Korea, and 35% for USA. Dryers can save up to 20% for EU, 35% for Korea, and 30% for USA. Air conditioners can achieve up to a global 30% energy savings, while EHS can achieve up to a global 15%. Dishwashers can save up to 40% for USA, 23% for EU, and 25% for Korea respectively.

Q : Could you provide a detailed explanation of the warranty?
A : The 20-year warranty applies exclusively to inverter motors and compressors in refrigerators, washers, and dryers sold in the European Union starting from July 2022. This warranty covers only Digital Inverter Technologies (motors/compressors) in refrigerators and washing machines manufactured by Samsung and its subcontracted manufacturers. It does not extend to any outsourced products. This warranty is applicable to select models, and the terms of service may vary by product and region.

Q : How much does the Less MicrofiberTM Cycle reduce microplastic emissions?
A : The Less MicrofiberTM Cycle reduces microplastic emissions by 54% when used with EcoBubbleTM technology in the washing machine. This result is based on testing conducted by the Ocean Wise Plastics Lab on a Samsung conventional 27-inch washing machine sold in Korea, using a 2kg load of 100% polyester hoodies, comparing the Synthetics cycle and the Less Microfiber cycle. Actual results may vary depending on the type of clothing and usage conditions. This feature is applicable to select models.

Q : When is the Auto Open Door feature useful?
A : Auto Open Door provides effortless and convenient operation for everyone. For instance, when your hands are full with groceries, a gentle touch on the touch sensor of the refrigerator door will cause it to open automatically. Similarly, the washing machine door opens automatically once the wash cycle is complete, and the dishwasher‚Äôs door does the same upon finishing its cycle.

title: How to use Samsung Wallet and Pay
description:
This is the official video guide on how to use Samsung Wallet. Ready to simplify your daily life with Samsung Wallet? ü§© Securely store and use your payment cards, transit cards, boarding passes, and more, all in one place. Learn more: http://smsng.co/SamsungWallet_How-to_yt

00:00 Intro
00:25 Set up Samsung Wallet
01:07 Register payment cards
01:45 Pay at stores
02:21 Add transit cards
02:56 Add tickets and more
03:42 Easy navigation
04:24 Use on Galaxy Watch

Follow these simple steps to use Samsung Wallet:
Step 1: Open the app, sign in with your Samsung Account, then set your authentication method (Fingerprint or PIN).
Step 2: Go to 'Add' ‚Üí 'Payment cards', scan your card, and enter the security details to register.
Step 3: In-store payment: Swipe up on screen ‚Üí verify your fingerprint ‚Üí tap your phone on the NFC/Samsung Pay reader.
Step 4: Transit card: 'Add' ‚Üí 'Add your transit card' ‚Üí choose card type and top-up amount ‚Üí register with 'Buy', then use it even without unlocking your phone.
Step 5: Tickets/boarding passes: Tap 'Add to Samsung Wallet' in your airline app, or add via 'Add to Samsung Wallet' after taking a QR/barcode screenshot of the ticket.
Step 6: Navigation/management: Swipe up to view cards, reorder, add, or remove; on foldables, you can access them quickly from FlexWindow.
Step 7: Watch payments: In Galaxy Wearable app ‚Üí Watch settings ‚Üí 'Wallet', set a PIN and tap 'Payment cards'; to pay, press and hold the Back key and tap an NFC reader.

Q: What‚Äôs the difference between Samsung Wallet and Samsung Pay?
A: Wallet is an app that integrates Pay plus Pass features‚Äîbeyond payments and points, it can also hold IDs, keys, and more.

Q: Can I pay with Galaxy Watch without a phone or network connection?
A: Yes. The watch can use Wallet without your smartphone and without Wi-Fi/cellular, and it even works in low-power mode.

description:

00:00 Intro

00:26 Active Noise Canceling

Follow these simple steps to use Adaptive Noise Control:
Step 1: Open the Galaxy Wearable app.
Step 2: Tap 'Adaptive' to turn on Adaptive Noise Control.
Step 3: Tap 'Active noise canceling' to turn on ANC and adjust the level.
Step 4: Tap 'Auto switch to ambient sound' to keep ambient sounds audible.
Step 5: Turn on 'Voice detect' so it automatically switches to Ambient sound when you speak.
Step 6: Turn on 'Siren detect' so it automatically switches to Ambient sound when a siren is detected.

Q: Do features work if I‚Äôm wearing only one earbud?
A: Ambient sound can be used with one earbud, but Adaptive sound and Active noise canceling require both earbuds.

Q: Can I adjust the ANC level?
A: Yes. In the Galaxy Wearable app, you can choose from five levels to set your preferred noise-cancellation intensity.

Follow these simple steps to get started with Galaxy Buds3 Series:
Step 1: Open the case and tap 'Connect' on your phone to pair.
Step 2: Insert the earbuds into your ear notches and adjust the angle for a comfortable fit.
Step 3: Swipe the Blade up/down to adjust volume.
Step 4: Pinch the Blade to play/pause, and pinch and hold to switch noise controls.
Step 5: In Galaxy Wearable ‚Üí 'Earbuds controls', set gestures and functions as you like.
Step 6: In 'Sound quality and effects', turn on 'Adjust sound to fit' and 'Ultra high quality (UHQ) audio', then choose your preferred sound in 'Equalizer'.

Q: Any tips for wearing?
A: Angle the lower mic on the Blade toward your mouth, check the L/R marks, then gently rotate forward/back to get a snug seal.

Q: Water resistance‚Äîis it okay to use in the rain?
A: Galaxy Buds3/Buds3 Pro have IP57 (dust/water resistance). That means up to 1 m of fresh water for 30 minutes. Use in seawater or pools isn‚Äôt recommended.

title: Voices of Galaxy: Johannes Floors | Samsung
description:
Voices of Galaxy is a series of real stories spotlighting Samsung Galaxy users who use their passion, creativity and determination along with technology, to make a positive impact on their own lives and their communities, and the world around them. Learn more: http://smsng.co/VOG-Johannes_yt

When German para-sprinter Johannes‚ÄØFloors was fitted with his first pair of running prosthetics at the age of 18, it was the first time he'd run since his amputation at 16. This new beginning was a blank canvas that opened up new possibilities and allowed him to first experience something he hadn‚Äôt realized was missing for the first sixteen years of his life.  

This is a story of a remarkable human who, through determination, meticulous engineering and desire to create an impact, went on to become a record-breaking Para-Athlete, and sets his sights on his way to the Paris 2024 Paralympic Games. 

For Johannes, mindset plays a crucial role to success. Johannes wants to help change perceptions of prosthetics, drive discussion across the Paralympic community and beyond, and help keep the next generation on track while he navigates the road ahead.

title: Meet the Generation17 Young Leaders: The Story of Efe Johnson | Samsung
description:
Read more about Efe and her story: http://smsng.co/Gen17_Efe_yt

Growing up in Nigeria, Generation17 Young Leader Efe Johnson experienced firsthand how a lack of access to women‚Äôs health education can create a cycle of silence and shame among young girls. Through her organization, Xari Africa, she strives to deliver safe and accessible reproductive and sexual health education to one million teenage girls across Africa. Through school visits and online academies, Xari Africa helps girls take control of their bodies and their futures. 

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals in less than 10 years. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change, peace and justice, to build a better future for all by 2030. To get involved, visit the Samsung Global Goals app here: http://smsng.co/SGG-App_Efe_yt

title: How to recap meeting | Galaxy AI | Galaxy Book4 Series | Samsung
description:
This is the official video guide on how to quickly summarize conversations with AI. The Copilot Phone Plugin is temporarily disabled due to product updates by Microsoft. The updated Phone Plugin is expected to be available in early 2025 depending on Microsoft‚Äôs release schedule. Please visit the Phone Plugin Support Page for more details. smsng.co/GalaxyBook4-support

Organize important details from a Text call or voice recording on your Galaxy phone, share them to your Galaxy Book4, and get a quick summary with Microsoft Copilot, a personalized AI assistant. Whether you‚Äôre a student or in business, you can now take your post-meeting productivity to the next level with this Galaxy AI laptop, powered by the Samsung ecosystem. Learn more: http://smsng.co/GalaxyBook4_Notes_yt

00:00 Intro
00:17 Text call and summarize
02:44 Transcribe and edit meeting notes

Follow these simple steps to summarize conversations with Copilot:
Step 1: Connect Galaxy Book and your phone with Link to Windows.
Step 2: Turn on 'Settings' ‚Üí 'Text call', and when a call comes in, respond by text on Galaxy Book.
Step 3: To summarize a meeting, open the call log or recorded file and use Copilot to create a quick summary.
Step 4: To enrich your notes, use Copilot to search/add images, then 'Quick Share' it with your team.

Q: When is Text call useful?
A: When you can‚Äôt answer a call directly during a meeting, you can respond by text on Galaxy Book.

Q: What‚Äôs the difference between call recording and Text call?
A: Text call is a real-time, text-based record; recording converts audio to text via Transcribe. Choose whichever is more convenient for your situation.

title: How to use Samsung Studio | Galaxy AI | Galaxy Book4 Series | Samsung
description:
This is the official video guide on how to use Samsung Studio to edit your videos. Create and edit your next masterpiece across devices with Samsung Studio. Offering seamless video editing within the Samsung ecosystem, Samsung Studio enables you to kickstart your edit on a Galaxy phone, Quick Share the project to your Galaxy Book4, and add the final touches on the bigger screen. Learn more: http://smsng.co/GalaxyBook4_Studio_yt

00:00 Intro
00:26 Shoot and edit on the phone
01:05 Share the project via Quick Share
01:24 Final touches on Galaxy Book4
02:38 Create thumbnail image

Follow these simple steps to use Samsung Studio:
Step 1: Shoot your video on your phone.
Step 2: Go to 'Gallery' ‚Üí 'Create' ‚Üí 'Go to Studio', start your basic edit.
Step 3: To fine-tune on a larger screen, 'Quick Share' the project to Galaxy Book.
Step 4: On Galaxy Book, edit up to four videos at the same time and apply effects such as music or stickers.
Step 5: Finish your video with 'Export', and if needed, create a thumbnail with 'Photo Assist'.

Q: Can I continue editing the exact same project I started on my phone?
A: Yes. Select 'Share project' ‚Üí 'Quick Share' to Galaxy Book, then open the file in Samsung Studio on Galaxy Book4 to continue working.

Q: What are the requirements for sharing via Quick Share?
A: Your Galaxy phone or tablet must be on One UI 6.1 or later, and Bluetooth must be turned on for sharing to work properly.

description:

Take your video calls to the next level with stunning picture clarity from your Galaxy phone‚Äîas powered by the Samsung ecosystem. Open up Windows Settings and head to 'Mobile Devices' from the Bluetooth & Devices page. title: Meet the Generation17 Young Leaders: The Story of Mock Yi Jun | Samsung
description:
Read more about Yi Jun and his story: http://smsng.co/Gen17_YiJun_yt

From a young age, Generation17 Young Leader, Mock Yi Jun, longed to find his professional calling. He wanted to explore different industries and gain experience before deciding on a career. This led him to create Advisory Singapore, a charity that connects students with career mentorship, resources and networking to help them find their passions. Today, Advisory Singapore has reached 200,000 young people and supported 3,000 mentees.

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals in less than 10 years. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change, peace and justice, to build a better future for all by 2030.

title: Meet the Generation17 Young Leaders: The Story of Zubair Junjunia | Samsung
description:
Read more about Zubair and his story: http://smsng.co/Gen17_Zubair_yt

Driven to level the academic playing field for all students, Generation17 Young Leader Zubair Junjunia founded ZNotes, a website for students to share their study materials for standardized testing. What began as a small online forum is now a global platform used by 4.7 million students and educators for open access to high-quality education.

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals in less than 10 years. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change, and peace and justice, to build a better future for all by 2030. To get involved, visit the Samsung Global Goals app here: http://smsng.co/SGG-App_Zubair_yt

#Generation17 #GlobalGoals #Samsung

description:
Introducing the new Samsung Bespoke NQ7000C wall oven that you can cook quickly and flexibly.
The Samsung built-in Combi Double Oven combines two cooking methods in one. Its upper cavity works as a microwave oven, but also includes a Power Convection system to cook food evenly, while ensuring it is crisp, brown and juicy. And the lower cavity is a normal oven.
Its Flex Duo‚Ñ¢ oven has upper and lower zones that work independently or together using a Dual Convection system. So you can cook a variety of dishes simultaneously using different temperatures and times.

description:
Introducing the new Samsung Bespoke NV7000C wall oven that lets you cook like a professional.  
AI Pro Cooking‚Ñ¢*, with an internal camera, recognizes* the ingredients and recommends the optimal cooking mode and setting.  You can remotely view the progress of your cooking and control the oven**, and create a time-lapse video of dishes cooking, and share it on social media. 

Its Flex Duo‚Ñ¢ oven has upper and lower zones that work independently or together using a Dual Convection system. So you can cook a variety of dishes simultaneously using different temperatures and times. 

* A dish should be placed in the center of the oven to achieve the best recognition. For more detailed information, please refer to the user guide enclosed with the package.
** Available on Android and iOS devices. A Wi-Fi connection and a Samsung account are required.

description:

title: Generation17 Introduces Young Leader Nora Altwaijri | Samsung
description:
Read more about Nora and her story: http://smsng.co/Gen17-Nora

Nora Altwaijri, a Generation17 Young Leader from Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, uses her passion for technology and background in software engineering to support young people who dream of making a positive impact in their communities. Nora developed the Sustainable University Initiative, a website that allows students to learn about the Global Goals and collaborate on solutions, like planting trees or cleaning a local beach. While piloting the website, Nora took her desire to support ambitious young people a step further and launched a grassroots initiative that provides youth with funding and mentorship opportunities. If we utilize technology and the energy of the youth generation, Nora is confident that we can build a future in which sustainability is part of everyday life.

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change, and peace and justice, to build a better future for all by 2030. Visit the Samsung Global Goals app to take action: http://smsng.co/SGG-App

title: Generation17 Introduces Young Leader Tamara Gondo | Samsung
description:
Read more about Tamara and her story: http://smsng.co/Gen17_Tamara

Tamara Gondo is a Generation17 Young Leader and the CEO of Liberty Society, a social enterprise that weaves refugee empowerment and environmental sustainability throughout its line of handcrafted clothing and accessories. The organization has provided upskilling opportunities and financial freedom to more than 100 refugees while helping over 500 families access education, food donations, and health services. With every eco-friendly t-shirt and bag, Tamara is opening possibilities for a better future.

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals in less than 10 years. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change, and peace and justice, to build a better future for all by 2030.

Visit the Samsung Global Goals app to take action: http://smsng.co/SGG-App

title: Voices of Galaxy: Meet the Bolivian Skateboarders Driving Social Change with Smartphones | Samsung
description:
Voices of Galaxy spotlights people who use their passion, creativity, and determination along with technology to make a positive impact on their own lives and their communities.

For ImillaSkate, skateboarding is more than a sport, it‚Äôs a life philosophy. As 9 women in their 20s, ImillaSkate resolved to use their passion for skating to instill a renewed sense of pride in cholitas, Bolivian indigenous women who were not always embraced by society. Donning polleras, the traditional skirts of their cholita culture, they took to the streets on their boards and have used smartphones to capture their cause every step of the way. Today, Galaxy technology is helping them continue to expand and engage with even more people around the world on social media, opening up new possibilities for them. 

From dynamic skating videos to important updates about their impact, smartphones are their most important tool for amplifying their message of inclusion. This is the story of Galaxy users Elli Buitrago, Belen Fajardo, Fabiola Gonzales, Brenda Mamani, Huara Medina, Susan Meza, Estefanny Morales, Daniela Santivanez and Deysi Tacuri - known collectively as ImillaSkate - who want the world to celebrate and embrace cholitas and women everywhere, both on and off the skateboard.

title: Voices of Galaxy: Meet the Veteran and Photographer Empowering Creativity with Smartphones | Samsung
description:
Voices of Galaxy spotlights people who use their passion, creativity, and determination along with technology to make a positive impact on their own lives and their communities. Learn more: http://smsng.co/VoicesofGalaxy-Brent

When photographer Brent Hall was medically discharged from the U.S. Navy in 2006 he found himself in the throes of PTSD and depression. He moved back to New Mexico and quickly realized that the more he grabbed his camera and took off in nature, the more he reconnected with himself and started to feel better. Today, Brent‚Äôs experience recognizing the therapeutic power of creative expression helps inspire nearly 85,000 people, including other veterans, who subscribe to his YouTube channel for approachable photography tips ‚Äî like how to take incredible images on Galaxy smartphones. This is the story of Galaxy user Brent Hall, who along with his wife and creative partner, Brittany, has a simple yet powerful message for people everywhere: Creativity can always open up positive experiences, and the best camera is the one you have on you!

#GalaxyS22 #VoicesofGalaxy #withGalaxy #Samsung

title: Generation17 Introduces Young Leader Yejin Choi | Samsung
description:
To get involved, visit the Samsung Global Goals App and visit us here: http://smsng.co/generation17_undp

Yejin Choi, a South Korean entrepreneur pioneering cognitive development solutions for children, is one of our featured Generation17 Young Leaders. With experience as a tutor and cognitive therapist, Yejin realized that a lot of children ‚Äì especially those with learning differences ‚Äì lack proper educational resources. To address this, Yejin turned to technology and founded DoBrain, an AI-based learning platform that utilizes mobile technology to offer immersive and interactive content. Since the launch in 2017, DoBrain has reached more than 600,000 children globally.  
 
Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals in less than 10 years. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges including poverty, inequality, climate change and peace and justice, to build a better future for all by 2030.

title: Exynos: Together with you (Holiday Ad 2021) | Samsung
description:
Dear fans,

After making it through 2021 together, we all remember this past year for the same thing: the pandemic.

Now new skin is growing over those wounds left by the pandemic, and we‚Äôre finding unexpected value in the scars left behind. That‚Äôs the value we call ‚Äútogetherness‚Äù. We were sick together. We worried together. We struggled together, and we found a way together. Even when we were far apart, we were closer than ever.

Our team also thought hard about what we could do to share the value of ‚Äútogetherness‚Äù. This short film is a small gift for our fans who have been with us throughout the pandemic. You waited patiently and you supported us. We may never meet face to face, but like the friends in this film, we still feel together. We know, more than anyone, what you expect from us, and we‚Äôre working harder than anyone to give you, our fans, the experiences you deserve. That‚Äôs our way of delivering on the promise of ‚Äútogetherness‚Äù. 

For all the fans out there who love gaming, we are preparing a small gift for you. We hope you have a warm and safe holiday and that you‚Äôll unbox that little gift with us in the New Year.

Sincerely,
The Exynos team

Learn more about Exynos processor: http://smsng.co/Exynos
#Samsung #Exynos #TogetherWithYou

title: Generation17 Introduces Young Leader Yurii Romashko | Samsung
description:
Yurii Romashko, a lawyer and digital advocate from Ukraine, is one of our featured Generation17 Young Leaders. Yurii is the co-founder and executive director of the Institute of Analysis and Advocacy (IAA), an organization that works to improve civil society by increasing transparency through digital tools. The group partners with government agencies to combat everything from price gouging during the COVID-19 pandemic to providing ‚Äúsmart city‚Äù resources to residents in Ukraine and abroad. 

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals in now less than 10 years. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals‚Äîor Sustainable Development Goals‚Äîprovide a framework to address pressing global challenges, including poverty, inequality, climate change and peace and justice, and build a better future for all by 2030.

To get involved, visit the Samsung Global Goals app and visit us here: http://smsng.co/generation17_undp

title: Knox Vault: Bringing Next-Level Security to Galaxy Devices | Samsung
description:
In the new normal of digital connectivity, privacy and security have never been more important. Samsung Knox, the security platform that keeps your Galaxy devices safe, has evolved to meet the growing demand for data protection. With Samsung Knox Vault, protection of your personal data is now taken to a whole new level.

Not only does it encrypt your personal data, but the Samsung Knox Vault processor keeps your important information safe, including sensitive information linked to apps like Samsung Pay. With Samsung Knox Vault storage, your data becomes isolated from the main operating system for even further protection. Best of all, it protects against a variety of attacks including voltage, temperature and laser attacks. 

Check out the video to learn more about how Samsung Knox Vault protects your most important information.

title: Voices of Galaxy: Meet the Underwater Cinematographer Changing the Way We View the Sea | Samsung
description:
Dongsik Kim has always been fascinated by nature. His love for the ocean fueled his ambition to become an underwater cinematographer and show the world what is hidden in the sea. title: Knox: Setting up key mapping for Microsoft Teams in VMware Workspace ONE | Samsung
description:

title: Generation17 Introduces Young Leader Sadya Tour√© | Samsung
description:
Sadya Tour√© from Mali is one of our featured Generation17 Young Leaders. Sadya witnessed female injustices and inequalities first-hand growing up in Africa, which inspired her to help women and girls take control of their lives. Through her work, Sadya has written a book on her experience and started, Mali Musso, an organization that empowers women through education to destigmatize gender-based violence.

Sadya‚Äôs goal is to fight for quality education, public health and an end to inequality ‚Äì ultimately showing young people it‚Äôs possible to make change.  

Generation17 is an initiative in partnership with the United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) that aims to harness technology to elevate the voices of young leaders around the globe who are working to achieve the Global Goals over the next 10 years. Established by the United Nations in 2015, the Global Goals - or Sustainable Development Goals - provide a framework to address pressing global challenges, including poverty, inequality, climate change and peace and justice, and build a better future for all by 2030.

To get involved, visit the Samsung Global Goals app and visit us here: http://smsng.co/generation17_undp
#Generation17 #Gen17 #GlobalGoals

title: Exynos: Thank you (Christmas Ad 2020) | Samsung
description:
Dear fans,

Although 2020 will be remembered as a year full of challenges, both global and personal, it also gave people time to reflect and think about what is most important to our lives. In rediscovering these personal values, we‚Äôve learned to cherish every precious moment we have with family and friends, and to believe in our inner strength and ability to tackle life‚Äôs challenges head on.

The same goes for the Exynos team. Now more than ever, we realize how important the support of our fans is towards going further. With a renewed confidence in the talent of our team, we have refocused our efforts to meet our fans‚Äô expectations by developing a whole new mobile processor.

To all of you, especially our fans that have waited patiently and supported us, we offer a heartfelt thank you. We hope this story will bring you a warm smile and that you have a happy holiday with family, friends and loved ones.

The Exynos team

title: [SAIF2020] Day2: Robotics - Daniel D. Lee | Samsung
description:
Session 4. Robotics

‚ÄúAI for Robots and People‚Äù

Recent achievements in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning have accomplished feats that surpass human performance; does this mean these techniques will soon scale to achieve machine superintelligence? This talk will examine some techniques used in modern machine learning algorithms: deep networks, state estimation, and reinforcement learning. I will show how these methods can be used to build more advanced robotic systems and discuss how they can be used to improve people‚Äôs daily lives.

For more information, visit our website: 
- Samsung Research: http://smsng.co/sr

title: [SAIF2020] Day2: Human Robot Interaction - Subbarao Kambhampati | Samsung
description:
Session 3. Human Robot Interaction

‚ÄúSynthesizing Interpretable Behavior for Human-Aware AI Systems‚Äù

As AI technologies enter our everyday lives at an ever increasing pace, there is a greater need for AI systems to work synergistically with humans. This requires AI systems to exhibit behavior that is explainable to humans. Synthesizing such behavior requires AI systems to reason not only with their own models of the task at hand, but also about the mental models of the human collaborators. Using several case-studies from our ongoing research, I will discuss how such multi-model planning forms the basis for explainable behavior.

For more information, visit our website: 
- Samsung Research: http://smsng.co/sr

title: [SAIF2020] Day2: Vision - Devi Parikh | Samsung
description:
Session 2. Vision

‚ÄúMultimodal and Creative AI Systems‚Äù

This talk will cover computer vision systems that humans can interact with via language, and AI systems that can enhance humans in their creative endeavors. In the first part of the talk I will describe our work on learning general visiolinguistic representations that can be used for a variety of vision & language tasks such as answering natural language questions about images, grounding natural language phrases in image regions, describing an image via a caption, etc. In the second part of the talk I will describe our work in automatically generating "dance" sequences from input music, generating abstract visualizations to represent salient aspects of a user's day and associated emotional states, neuro-symbolic generative art, and evaluating collaboration mechanisms in the context of sketching.

For more information, visit our website: 
- Samsung Research: http://smsng.co/sr
tags: ['SamsungAIFourm', 'SAIF', 'SAIF2020']
caption: false

title: [SAIF2020] Day2: Natural Language Processing - Christopher Manning | Samsung
description:
Session 1. Natural Language Processing

‚ÄúNatural Language Understanding and Conversational AI‚Äù

Natural language processing (NLP) has made dramatic advances over the last three years, ranging from deep generative models for text-to-speech, such as WaveNet, through the extensive deployment of deep contextual language models, such as BERT. Pre-training with models like BERT has significantly raised the performance of almost all NLP tasks, allowed much better domain adaptation, and brought us human-level performance for tasks like answering straightforward factual questions. New neural language models have also brought much more fluent language generation. On the one hand, we should not be too impressed by these linguistic savants: Things like understanding the consequences of events in a story or performing common sense reasoning remain out of reach. But on the other hand, I will discuss how we now live in an era where there are many good commercial uses of NLP, with much of the heavy lifting already done in the construction of large but downloadable models. I present some of our work on understanding how these models learn to be so proficient, and how we can build new types of pre-trained models that are much more compute efficient. Finally, I turn to conversational agents, where neural models can produce accurate task-based dialog agents and more effective open domain social bots.

For more information, visit our websites: 
- Samsung Research: http://smsng.co/sr

title: [SAIF 2020] Day 1: Intelligibility Throughout the Machine Learning Life Cycle - Jenn Wortman Vaughan
description:
People play a central role in the machine learning life cycle. Consequently, building machine learning systems that are reliable, trustworthy, and fair requires that relevant stakeholders‚Äîincluding developers, users, and the people affected by these systems‚Äîhave at least a basic understanding of how they work. Yet what makes a system ‚Äúintelligible‚Äù is difficult to pin down. Intelligibility is a fundamentally human-centered concept that lacks a one-size-fits-all solution. I will explore the importance of evaluating methods for achieving intelligibility in context with relevant stakeholders, ways of empirically testing whether intelligibility techniques achieve their goals, and why we should expand our concept of intelligibility beyond machine learning models to other aspects of machine learning systems, such as datasets and performance metrics.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2020] Day 1: Towards End-to-End Speech Recognition - Tara Sainath | Samsung
description:
End-to-end models allow us to represent the entire speech recognition pipeline (i.e., conventional acoustic, pronunciation and language models) by one neural network. This has huge implications for privacy, reliability and latency. In this talk, we will discuss the research developments around E2E models that have allowed it to reach the accuracy of conventional models, at a fraction of the model size and reduced latency. In addition, we will present further benefits of these models with respect to multi-lingual speech recognition.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2020] Day 1: From Few-Shot Adaptation to Uncovering Symmetries - Chelsea Finn | Samsung
description:
Machine learning systems are often designed under the assumption that they will be deployed as a static model in a single static region of the world. However, the world is constantly changing, such that the future no longer looks exactly like the past, and even in relatively static settings, the system may be deployed in new, unseen parts of its world. While such continuous shifts in the data distribution can place major challenges on models acquired in machine learning, the model need not be static either: it can and should adapt. In this talk, I‚Äôll discuss how we can allow deep networks to be robust to such distribution shift via adaptation. I will focus on meta-learning algorithms that enable this adaptation to be fast, first introducing the concept of meta-learning, then briefly overviewing several successful applications of meta-learning ranging from robotics to drug design, and finally discussing several recent works at the frontier of meta-learning research.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2020] Day 1: Towards Discovering Casual Representations - Yoshua Bengio | Samsung
description:
Up to now deep learning has focused on learning representations which are useful in many applications but differ from the kind of high-level representations humans can communicate with natural language and capture semantic (verbalizable) variables and their causal dependencies. Capturing causal structure is important for many reasons: (a) it allows an agent to take appropriate decisions (interventions) by having a good causal model of its effects, (b) it can lead to robustness with respect to changes in distribution (a major current limitation of state-of-the-art machine learning), and (c) it makes it easier to understand natural language (which refers to such causal concepts, the semantic variables named with words) and thus interact more meaningfully with humans. Whereas causality research has focused on inference (like how strong is the causal effect of A on B?) and to a lesser extent on causal discovery (is A a direct cause of B?), an important open question to which deep learning researchers can contribute is that of discovering causal representations, i.e., transformations from low-level sensory data to high-level representations of causal variables, where the high-level variables are not always labeled by humans. This must necessarily be done at the same time as one learns the structure of the causal graph which links these variables since both are generally unknown. This talk will report on early efforts towards these objectives, as part of a larger research programme aimed at expanding deep learning from system 1 (unconscious) processing to system 2 (conscious-level) processing of semantic variables.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2019] Day2: Geometric Deep Learning for Forecasting and Semi-supervised Learning - Joan Bruna
description:
Geometric Deep Learning is an emerging paradigm to process graph-structured data with end-to-end trainable models, Graph Neural Networks (GNNs), with the ability to leverage prior knowledge about the data domain while offering large expressive power. Such attractive tradeoff has resulted in state-of-the-art performance over diverse domains, ranging from social networks, biology, knowledge bases, or finance. In this talk, I will present recent advances in our group covering both theory and applications. On the theory side, we quantify both the approximation power of GNN architectures and their stability to graph perturbations, resulting in a principled architecture design. We will illustrate these theoretical advances with applications in semi-supervised learning and forecasting in dynamic graphs modeling Social Network data, and discuss broader applications to recommender systems and fraud detection.

#SAIF
#SamsungAIForum
#SR
#SamsungResearch

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 2: Symbolic Logic meets Machine Learning: Towards Reliable AI ‚Äì Vaishak Belle
description: Artificial Intelligence (AI) provides many opportunities to improve private and public life, and it has enjoyed significant investment. Indeed, discovering patterns and structures in large troves of data in an automated manner is a core component of data science. Machine learning currently drives applications in computational biology, natural language processing and robotics. However, such a highly positive impact is coupled with a significant challenge: when can we convincingly deploy these methods in our workplace? For example, can we provide prior knowledge and suggestions to the learning modules? Can we learn interpretable symbolic structures from data? In this talk, we look at the fundamental problem of unifying reasoning and learning, and how this enables a systematic way to integrate human knowledge and data-driven learning methods. We will then briefly consider how that unification may help us take steps towards a commonsensical, transparent and responsible AI.
tags: ['SAIF', 'Samsung AI Forum', 'SR', 'Samsung Research']
caption: false

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 2: Rational Recurrences for Empirical Natural Language Processing ‚Äì Noah Smith
description:
Despite their often-discussed advantages, deep learning methods largely disregard theories of both learning and language. This makes their prediction behavior hard to understand and explain. In this talk, I will present a path toward more understandable (but still "deep") natural language processing models, without sacrificing accuracy. Rational recurrences comprise a family of recurrent neural networks that obey a particular set of rules about how to calculate hidden states, and hence correspond to parallelized weighted finite-state pattern matching. Many recently introduced models turn out to be members of this family, and the weighted finite-state view lets us derive some new ones. I'll introduce rational RNNs and present some of the ways we have used them in NLP. My collaborators on this work include Jesse Dodge, Hao Peng, Roy Schwartz, and Sam Thomson.  

#SAIF
#SamsungAIForum
#SR
#SamsungResearch

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 2: Supersizing and Empowering Visual and Robot Learning ‚Äì Abhinav Gupta‚îÇSamsung
description:
Supersizing and Empowering Visual and Robot Learning Abstract: In the last decade, we have made significant advances in the field of computer vision thanks to supervised learning. But this passive supervision of our models has now become our biggest bottleneck. In this talk, I will discuss our efforts towards scaling up and empowering visual learning. First, I will show how the amount of labeled data is a crucial factor in learning. I will then describe how we can overcome the passive supervision bottleneck by self-supervised learning. Next, I will discuss how embodiment is crucial for learning ‚Äì our agents live in the physical world and need the ability to interact in the physical world. Towards this goal, I will finally present our efforts in large-scale learning of embodied agents in robotics. Finally, I will discuss how we can move from passive supervision to active exploration ‚Äì the ability of agents to create their own training data.

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 1: New Perspectives on Generative Adversarial Networks - Simon Lacoste-Julien
description:
Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) are a popular generative modelling approach known for producing appealing samples, but their theoretical properties are not yet fully understood, and they are notably difficult to train. In the first part of this talk, I will provide some insights on why GANs are a more meaningful framework to model high dimensional data like images than the more traditional maximum likelihood approach, interpreting them as "parametric adversarial divergences" and rooting the analysis with statistical decision theory. In the second part of the talk, I will address the difficulty of training GANs from the optimization perspective by importing tools from the mathematical programming literature. I will survey the "variational inequality" framework which contains most formulations of GANs introduced so far, and present theoretical and empirical results on adapting the standard methods (such as the extragradient method) from this literature to the training of GANs.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 1: New Directions in Automatic Text Summarization - Jackie Cheung | Samsung
description:
Automatic text summarization is an important tool for enhancing users' ability to make decisions in the face of overwhelming amounts of data. Key to making this technology useful and practical is to have high-performing systems that work on a variety of texts and settings. However, existing systems are usually developed and tested on standard research benchmarks based on news texts. In this talk, I discuss how current systems exploit biases in these benchmark tasks in order to perform well without deeply understanding the contents of the input. In particular, they heavily exploit the fact that important sentences tend to appear near the beginning of news articles. I present our lab's extractive summarization system, BanditSum, which frames summarization as a contextual bandit problem, and our efforts to induce BanditSum to focus on both the position of a sentence and its contents in making content selection decisions, leading to improved summarization performance. Next, I argue that effective summarization requires advances in abstractive summarization, which analyzes the contents of the source texts in order to generate novel summary sentences. However, existing datasets do not require or support the learning of the type of reasoning and generalization which would demonstrate abstraction's utility. I discuss the ongoing work in my lab in this direction, both from the perspective of analyzing and improving existing abstractive approaches, and from the perspective of developing new datasets and tasks in which abstraction is necessary.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 1: Three Flavors of Neural Sequence Generation - Kyunghyun Cho | Samsung
description:
Standard neural sequence generation methods assume a pre-specified generation order, such as left-to-right generation. Despite its wild success in recent years, there's a lingering question of whether this is necessary and if there is any other way to generate such a sequence in an order automatically learned from data without having to pre-specify it or relying on external tools. I will discuss in this talk three alternatives; parallel decoding, recursive set prediction, and insertion-based generation.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 1: Adapting and Explaining Deep Learning for Autonomous Systems - Trevor Darrell
description:
Learning of layered or "deep" representations has recently enabled low-cost sensors for autonomous vehicles and efficient automated analysis of visual semantics in online media. But these models have typically required prohibitive amounts of training data, and thus may only work well in the environment they have been trained in. I‚Äôll describe recent methods in adversarial adaptive learning that excel when learning across modalities and domains. Further, these models have been unsatisfying in their complexity--with millions of parameters--and their resulting opacity. I‚Äôll report approaches which achieve explainable deep learning models, including both introspective approaches that visualize compositional structure in a deep network, and third-person approaches that can provide a natural language justification for the classification decision of a deep model.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: [SAIF 2019] Day 1: Towards Compositional Understanding of the World by Deep Learning - Yoshua Bengio
description:
Humans are much better than current AI systems at generalizing out-of-distribution. What ingredients can bring us closer to that level of competence? We propose 4 ingredients combined: (a) meta-learning (to learn end-to-end to generalize to modified distributions, sampled from a distribution over distributions), (b) designing modular architectures with the property that modules are fairly independent of each other and interacting sparsely while made to be composed in new ways easily, (c) capturing causal structure decomposed into independent mechanisms so as to correctly infer the effect of interventions by agents which modify the data distribution, and (d) building better and more stable models of the invariant properties of possibly changing environments by taking advantage of the interactions between the learner and its environment to learn semantic high-level variables and their interactions, i.e., adopting an agent perspective on learning to benefit deep learning of abstract representations. The last ingredient implies that learning purely from text is not sufficient and we need to strive for learning agents which build a model of the world, to which linguistic labels can be associated, i.e., performing grounded language learning. Whereas this agent perspective is reminiscent of deep reinforcement learning, the focus is not on how deep learning can help reinforcement learning (as a function approximation black box) but rather how the agent perspective common in reinforcement learning can help deep learning discover better representations of knowledge.

#SAIF #SamsungAIForum

For more info, visit our page:
#SAIT(Samsung Advanced Institute of Technology): http://smsng.co/sait

title: Global Film Industry Professionals' Review about Samsung Cinema LED
description:

Designated as one of the official theaters at the Busan International Film Festival (BIFF), Samsung Cinema LED screen, delivering a next-generation theater experience, has won raves from global film industry professionals, movie critics, and viewers.

Samsung Cinema LED Screen was installed at the Lotte Cinema in Centum City, Busan this September, where audiences were treated to the film ‚ÄòMother!‚Äô, with actress Jennifer Lawrence and directed by Darren Aronofsky. At this year‚Äôs BIFF, which is Asia‚Äôs largest film festival, around 300 movies from 75 countries were showcased throughout the festival. Samsung Cinema LED received high marks from film industry professionals, in particular for its realistic screen and color depiction keeping to the original intent of directors and producers.

title: SDC 2017 Session: The Impact of Connecting Cars into the Internet of Things
description:
Samsung Developer Conference 2017 Session
Speaker: Stephen L. Surhigh - Harman

The invention of the automobile changed many aspects of people's lives.  Infrastructure improvements such as paving dirt roads resulted in social and economic changes like enabling families to take vacations away from home.  Historians agree that the automobile has had a significant historical impact on our modern lifestyles.  
As autonomous driving evolves and vehicles become more connected in the IoT space, the need for connectivity, data consumption, security and innovation become exponentially more important.  The presentation will look at the automobile's expected impact on the IoT space and will introduce the Harman Ignite platform. title: SDC 2017 Session: The Future of Human and Machine Intelligence: Separating Fact From Fiction
description:
Samsung Developer Conference 2017 Session
Speakers: Adam Cheyer - Samsung, Bryan Johnson - Kernel, Ray Perrault - SRI International, Tom Standage - The Economist
Machine learning, better known as artificial intelligence (AI), has become one of the hottest topics in technology. Things that were once science fiction - computers that can talk, self-driving cars, and using your face to unlock things - are now real. But AI's rapid progress raises many questions. How quickly will the technology be adopted, and what will the implications be? How will improvements in AI change our perception of our own intelligence, and what it means to be human? How might AI and brain-computer interfaces allow humans to enhance themselves? This expert panel will cut through the noise of the AI debate, separating fact from fiction, giving you a better understanding of the state of AI - and equipping you with the mental toolkit you need to make sense of its development in the years to come.
tags: ['intelligence', 'AI']
caption: false

title: SDC 2017 Session: Future Design for No UI
description:
Samsung Developer Conference 2017 Session
Speaker: Jared Ficklin - argodesign

As we go about our day-to-day lives deeply immersed in our smartphones, we may come to believe that the future will be mostly things we see on the screens in our hands. But the future holds much more. We believe many of our usual mobile experiences will leave the device, moving instead to smart TVs or other glass interfaces, and many more will not engage our eyes at all but other senses, as we already see with wearables. Join us as we indulge in some futurism. How can we see things normally not seen? How can we have experiences without user interfaces? What could the next pattern of computing look like and how would that impact products, design and our increasingly digital lifestyles?

Samsung Developer Conference 2017 Session
Speakers: Kwanghyun Koh - Samsung, Kevin Tucker - Spotify

Samsung dominates global smart TV market for many years, and users are using it not only to consume video content but also to use other smart TV apps in various domains. Samsung smart TV analytics have been used to help Samsung smart TV app developers to understand their user behavior to improve the overall app experience while enabling them to tap into new business opportunities. In this session, we will present details of how to better utilize Samsung smart TV analytics to better understand your smart TV app users. It will include a demo of how it works, KPI data types, advanced features, and so on. title: SDC 2017 Session: Can Using IoT and AI Help Solve the World's Problems?
description:
Samsung Developer Conference 2017 Session
Speakers: Chantal Botana, Kourosh Karimkhany - The Weather Company, an IBM Business, Sridhar Sudarsan - IBM, Alison Walker - IBM Watson Content and IoT Platform
Today's world is more interconnected than ever before. The ability to access copious amounts of data in an instant across numerous touch points has changed the way we interact and understand one another and the world around us. The integration of Augmented Intelligence (AI) with IoT devices provides a unique opportunity to gain a better understanding of these various data points, and allows us to make informed decisions that can not only improve, but even potentially save lives. Within this panel, AI and IoT experts from IBM and IBM's The Weather Company will discuss some of the world's biggest climate, environmental and health-related challenges, and how we can leverage AI, machine learning, IoT devices and crowdsourced data to create sustainable, intelligent solutions.

title: SDC 2016 Session: An Introduction to ARTIK IDE Powered by Eclipse Che
description:
Speaker: Tyler Jewell,¬†CEO,¬†Codenvy
What happens when on-demand workspaces powered by Docker are transformed into a new kind of IDE for IOT? This session introduces the ARTIK IDE, built upon Eclipse Che the next-generation Eclipse IDE supported by SAP, Codenvy, Red Hat, Samsung and Microsoft. We'll show you how a cloud IDE makes developing IoT applications fast, powerful, and fun. We will review how Che provides utilities for professional and makers including intellisense, content assist, git version control, ARTIK stack and SDK runtimes, device discovery, debugging, Android extensions, and plugins.

The ARTIK IDE is provided on a workspace server, which lets workspaces move between computers, shared by multiple users, and embedded within other systems.  Get up and running within minutes to build the next-generation of IoT apps.

title: SDC 2016 Session: Write Once and Run Everywhere with TOAST for Smart TV
description:
Speaker: Cristian Valladares, Senior Engineer, Samsung
Developing and maintaining multiple apps for the different smart TV platforms (Samsung legacy platform, Samsung Tizen TV, WebOS TV, and others) is cumbersome and resource intensive. Samsung‚Äôs new open source project TOAST allows you to develop a single cross-platform solution for all your TV web applications. In this session you will learn how to use TOAST to develop a single TV web application for use across multiple platforms. You will also see case studies and gain access to technical documents and guides for launching and optimizing the apps.
